Oct 3 2008 	This is the best hostel in London	I was there with my girlfriend for 4 nights and we got a twin room (the double was way to expensive compared to the twin because of the ensuite facilities).First of all the location: Gunterstone Road is outside the centre, in West Kensington and it's a nice residential place. It's in the middle between West Kensington and Baron's Court tube stations, which are both just 5 minutes far: the first features a nice pub outside where to have a last beer or a meal. Even though Ace Hotel is located a bit outside, it's easy to return also at late night (after the tube closes) as bus number 9 brings you to Kensington (Olympia) and then you can either take another bus to West Kensington tube station or walk 7-10 minutes (we always chose the latter option).Now to the hotel: it immediately felt relaxing, with the giant Connect 4 where you can play (it's a bit noisy when you put the giant coins in, but nobody really bothers. ;-)). The corridors, with all the steep stairs, were just delicious (but you'll have to be fit if you bag is heavy :-)). The room was compact but very clean (the whole hostel was very clean!), and although it had no bathroom it featured a sink. The shared bathroom was near and almost always empty, as were the showers, so it was very handy to use.The staff was very helpful, even though (like others noted here on TripAdvisor) they're sometimes a bit serious. They're not rude at all, but maybe it feels they're too &quot;professional&quot; for a hostel - but they're always way better than the &quot;very nice but useless&quot; found in other hostels.The breakfast is basic but OK. I had it a couple of times and then decided to use Starbucks: I go to the UK every now and then and there are no Starbucks shops in Italy, so I like to go to them. ;-)All in all: STAY HERE, it's inexpensive and it'll be a good experience!	
