Jun 25 2006	Fantastic!	While the Ace Hotel may not be in the heart of Central London it makes up for that in many other ways. First of all it is very easy to get to via the tube from Heathrow Airport. Simply take the Picadilly Line to Baron's Court and get off. It's about a 30 minute tube ride, but it's cheaper than taking a cab or the Heathrow Express. It's also insanely clean. The bedrooms are very comfortable, but bring your own lock for the locker to avoid having to pay for one so you can lock your things up. Also, word to the wise, bring an extra pillow. You only get one here so unless you're fine with just folding it in half, which I did and I was perfectly happy with that, bring an extra. Bring shower shoes as well, unless you have an ensuite. The bathrooms were easy to find, just walk around your area and you can easily find 3-4 bathrooms that are easy to get to. Always wear these when going to the bathroom, because you never know when someone may have flooded the bathroom while taking a shower. When I say flooded I mean the floor is a bit wet, not anything drastic. Just wear shoes. Free breakfast is nice, but the croissants are dry and the OJ is usually watered down. However, cereal is cereal and you can't really go wrong there. If you dip the croissant in jam you're good to go. The Ace Hotel is incredibly secure too! Which was relieving. You have your key card to your room and you must use that to get inside of the hostel, into your wing, and then once again to get into your room. The internet price is a bit steep one pound for half an hour, which I gladly paid at times I was missing my friends, but it was just easier to find a cheaper internet cafe and pay there. The bar area is nice, drinks are reasonably priced, but even the employees will tell you to not buy their food. It's Top Ramen-esque. What you need to do is ask to see their delivery menus. They have chinese (SO GOOD) and italian food menus, among others, to order from. All you have to do is write down your name, room, and what you want and the LOVELY staff will call in the order for you! Just make sure to be there when the food arrives. The delivery was cheap, I paid about $20 for two people to eat dinner, which is what I pay in the US anyways. The big screen TV is amazing, it's high def, which is cool to see. It's a fantastic hostel with tons of nice people and the guests are always pleasant, interesting, and funny. I highly recommend this hostel and will most definitely stay there again when I visit London.	
