Nov 28 2005	Great Value!	After searching through MANY &quot;inexpensive&quot; options for a night in London, the Ace was a great choice. We had no trouble with our booking, the rooms and showers were very clean, and the decor fun and modern. We took a room without an ensuite shower/toilet and have no regrets--very acceptable even for us &quot;modest&quot; americans! The location felt very safe even late at night. Their website offers a great representation of what you'll get.	
Nov 28 2005	Great Place	I've stayed in quite a few hostels in London over the past 15 years and this one is so far the BEST.It's situated in a very nice area with the underground close by. It's not right in the middle of the city but it doesn't take you long ot get to places.The Staff was really friendly and helpful. The hostel itself has a nice atmosphere, is comfy and clean. The rooms are pretty basic but clean and that is what counts. The hostel could do with a couple of more bathrooms/showers. It would be helpful if the hostel would put up signs of where the nearest bathroom is. Would save time as you have to wander around first for a while until you get your bearings.	
Nov 3 2005	it deserves # 1 rating	Stayed at the Ace Hotel for three nights end of October. Immaculate, quiet, very secure &amp; deserves its star status among the hostels of London. For two nights, we stayed in a twin room (comfortable bunkbeds) with facilities across the hall..never waited for a shower, bath or WC. For our last night in London we booked into a twin ensuite..again bunkbeds but no problem for this middle aged couple! We used the internet access (high speed) for 1£ for 30 minutes. We welcomed the laundry facilities on our last morning. The garden patio under the propane heaters was a lovely place to entertain our London friend. Bar service along with snacks was great. The included continental breakfast offered several cereals, toast, fruit juice, hot chocolate, instant coffee and tea in an airy and clean dining room. On our last morning, we relaxed in one of the two lounges both complete with TVs and one with a pool table. Both had lovely comfortable leather sofas.We would stay here anytime. Sharon &amp; CarlManitoba, Canada	
Oct 15 2005	ok for money	I stayed in a room with four beds on the basement. It has en suite bathroom too. The price is 23.50 pounds per person, so we stayed for three nights. The room is clean, but they don't make our beds everyday, only collect rubbish in the bin. There is nothing in the room, and no kitchen to share. Although for the room and price, it should have facilities like a youth hostel. I went to ask for hot water, a staff said I have to pay 40p. There is a lovely bar on the ground floor with a long list of drinks, and also Internet at 1 pound for 30 mins, and 1.50 for an hour. The location is find, kind of residential area in West Kensington.	
Aug 17 2005	Quite Pleasant	The hostel is very clean &amp; modern - situated on a quiet residential street. There is not much in the area but the hostel is located close to Barons Court Tube Station on Piccadilly line &amp; West Kensington on District line, nicely between the airport and city centre. There was some confusion checking in, as receptionist would not split the price between all guests (7) got very tricky and took some time - we arrived late (12.30am). We stayed in a 4-bed dorm, very small room that left little space for luggage. The bathroom was very small and shower just ok. You have to rent towels, hairdryer etc most things cost £1 each. Breakfast is included which was a selection of cereals, toast, tea &amp; coffee etc. Check out time was quite early 10.00am. The Staff were very strict with check out times and will stand at your door ensuring that you are packing/leaving. Garden area is pleasant but they ensure a curfew of 10.45pm due to local residents - this includes rooms that have a balcony area. All in all it was a pleasant stay.	
Aug 15 2005	Absolutely the Best!	Wow! When planning our trip to London, I searched the interenet for 3 hours one day trying to find a place to stay. All other hostels seemed to have horrible reviews and the cheap to middle range hotels even got bad reviews, too. But then I came upon the Ace Hotel (hostel) website. I had high expecations for this place and all of them were met, if not exceeded. The hostel was very modern and fun looking. The place was SO clean! There were crisp white bedsheets and duvets, the carpet was super clean, and the community bathrooms were always very clean, too. I was so amazed with this place! It was definitely not the &quot;party&quot; type hostel but the staff was friendly and there were friends to be made if that's what you're after. After traveling all over Europe for a year and staying at countless hotels and hostels, this by far was the best place ever. Stay here!	
